# Cohort 1 Impact Report

## 1. Cohort Overview
- **Cohort Duration:** Sept 30 – Nov 21, 2021  
- **Number of Participants:** 277  
- **Delivery Mode:** Online
- **Mentors:** 14 Bitcoin Experts  

This report summarizes the impact of Cohort 1, including participant outcomes, projects, community engagement, and long-term initiatives.

---

## 2. Quantitative Impact

| Metric                                  | Result                 |
|----------------------------------------|-------------------------|
| Total Participants Trained             | 277                     |
| Participants graduated                 | 63                      |
| Active Participation in Community Forum | 80+ participants       |
| Local Bitcoin Adoption Initiatives      | 5 community campaigns  |
| Participants Implementing Bitcoin Use Cases | 63                 |
| Number of Educational Resources Created | 12 (videos, guides)    |

---

## 3. Participant Demographics

| Category             | Number / Percentage |
|----------------------|------------------|
| Age 15–20            | 77 (25.8%)       |
| Age 21–30            | 201 (67.4%)      |
| Age 31–40            | 18 (6%)          |
| Age 41-55            | 2 (0.7%)         |
| Gender - Female      | 89 (29.9%)       |
| Gender - Male        | 209 (70.1%)     |
13 African Countries represented.

---

## 4. Project Impact

### 4.1 Bitcoin Adoption Map
- Mapped 12 merchants in Ilorin accepting Bitcoin.
- 4 new merchants onboarded during cohort duration.
- 1 interactive map shared with community.

### 4.2 Lightning Network Demo
- Participants conducted 50+ microtransactions successfully.
- Documentation and video tutorial created for future cohorts.

### 4.3 Community Education Campaign
- Reached 500+ people through webinars, workshops, and social media.


---

## 5. Qualitative Impact

### 5.1 Testimonials
> “The program opened my eyes to the real use of Bitcoin in Africa. I now see how it can empower local businesses and communities.” –Fadilat M.  

> “I was able to implement a Lightning payment solution for my business. It’s a game-changer for cross-border transactions.” – Imran  

> “The mentorship and community support made me confident to launch my first Bitcoin adoption initiative in my city.” – Folahan

### 5.2 Stories of Change
- **Community Merchant Initiative:** A participant onboarded 4 small businesses to accept Bitcoin in Ilorin within a week.  
- **Educational Outreach:** A group of participants ran a 1-day Bitcoin workshop in a rural community, reaching 50+ students and entrepreneurs.  

---

## 6. Metrics & KPIs for Future Cohorts
- Goal: Increase participant completion rate to **95%+**.  
- Goal: Expand local Bitcoin adoption initiatives from **10 → 20**.  
- Goal: Increase community reach from **500 → 1500 people**.  
- Goal: Generate **20+ educational resources** for community use.  
